Lomak says reserves ' value rose to $ 492 mln . Lomak Petroleum Inc said the value of its proven reserves more than doubled in 1996 to $ 492 million , mainly as a result of its acquisition of $ 400 million worth of properties from American Cometra . During the year , reserves rose 29 percent to 384 billion of cubic feet equivalent ( Bcfe ) , the company added . The company said it added 387 Bcfe of proven reserves in 1996 , including the acquisition , which was announced January 2 . The company said it expects to close the acquisition within 30 days . A Lomak spokesman said the increase in reserves would mean the company would report increased earnings and cash flow for fiscal 1997 but would not provide specific figures . 
